text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia formidabilis is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields regions of Western Australia.The diffuse pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 0.6 metres (1 to 2 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
